= \begin{bmatrix} 120 & 100 \\ 96 & 80 \end{bmatrix}
\]
So, the cost matrix for Week 2 is:
\(
\begin{bmatrix} 120 & 100 \\ 96 & 80 \end{bmatrix}
\) dollars.

(b) Calculate the cost matrix for Week 1 by multiplying \( M_1 \) by \( C \):
\[
